1
00:00:01,720 --> 00:00:03,680
Mom, I lost my job.

2
00:00:05,485 --> 00:00:07,720
I can't help him
with anything at all.

3
00:00:07,745 --> 00:00:09,400
I want to cry.

4
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:12,000
What's this?

5
00:00:12,025 --> 00:00:14,382
The Sacred Beckoning Cat Talisman.

6
00:00:14,407 --> 00:00:19,280
Keep it to for luck, fortune,
happiness, and prosperity.

7
00:00:19,280 --> 00:00:23,600
Once the rainstorm passes
may only good things come to you.

8
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,695
No, I don't want it.

9
00:00:25,720 --> 00:00:29,285
Isn't that the tarot reader
from last time?

10
00:00:29,817 --> 00:00:31,840
He changed his style?

11
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:33,160
Yeah.

12
00:00:33,920 --> 00:00:36,150
I've been a company
worker for so long.

13
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,320
I don't know
how to do anything else.

14
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,370
Well, you get to try new things.

15
00:00:40,760 --> 00:00:43,232
- Open up to new experiences.
- At 50 years old?

16
00:00:45,698 --> 00:00:46,698
If I...

17
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:51,040
can't pay the premium this year?

18
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:55,880
You're not my only child, you know.

19
00:00:57,520 --> 00:01:00,815
Why do you have to
carry everything alone?

20
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:03,003
You don't have to
carry it all alone.

21
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:05,813
Endure a bit longer,

22
00:01:06,387 --> 00:01:07,713
soon the stars

23
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:11,206
will move to a new position.

24
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,111
Hang in there.
The stars will move soon.

25
00:01:40,871 --> 00:01:43,451
Ohn, take these...

26
00:01:43,476 --> 00:01:45,684
and return them to
your grandma in Nakhon Nayok.

27
00:01:45,709 --> 00:01:47,040
Come on, Mom.

28
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:50,095
It's been so long, she's probably
forgotten all about them.

29
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:52,812
She gave them to you,
so just keep them.

30
00:01:52,812 --> 00:01:55,205
- There's no need to return them.
- You're so stubborn.

31
00:01:55,205 --> 00:01:56,980
You never do what I ask.

32
00:01:57,005 --> 00:02:00,910
You return them to
your grandma, and your father.

33
00:02:01,512 --> 00:02:04,032
I don't want
any karmic debt to follow me.

34
00:02:04,065 --> 00:02:07,080
Let's end it in this lifetime.

35
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,080
Do you understand?

36
00:02:38,423 --> 00:02:41,895
Mom, there's so much stuff here.

37
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:44,390
You should have hired
someone to help you pack.

38
00:02:45,205 --> 00:02:46,640
Ohn...

39
00:02:47,575 --> 00:02:50,062
I had to close the shop
because I couldn't keep trying

40
00:02:50,062 --> 00:02:53,495
to compete with those
24-hour convenience stores.

41
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:57,920
Where would I get the money
to hire people to pack all this?

42
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:00,796
So I ask my son to help me.

43
00:03:04,126 --> 00:03:07,760
If you two want anything, take it.

44
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:10,107
Canned fish, bottled water,

45
00:03:10,107 --> 00:03:12,605
and this laundry detergent.
Take a bunch of it!

46
00:03:12,605 --> 00:03:15,960
- Oh, thanks!
- Sure.

47
00:03:16,912 --> 00:03:18,400
- Hey, Mom.
- Yes, dear?

48
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,400
You've been running
this shop every single day.

49
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,880
Won't you be lonely
once it's closed?

50
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:24,120
Not at all.

51
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:26,823
I have plenty of things to do.

52
00:03:26,823 --> 00:03:29,040
And I know everyone around here.

53
00:03:29,040 --> 00:03:33,234
Anywhere I go,
people greet me and talk to me.

54
00:03:33,234 --> 00:03:35,698
- I won't be lonely.
- Oh.

55
00:03:35,723 --> 00:03:37,136
- Jee.
- Huh?

56
00:03:37,136 --> 00:03:41,415
She's the Miss Congeniality.
You don't have to worry about her.

57
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,560
Take that.

58
00:03:42,585 --> 00:03:45,972
In that case,
closing down is a good thing.

59
00:03:45,972 --> 00:03:47,488
You can finally rest.

60
00:03:47,793 --> 00:03:48,793
Yes.

61
00:03:49,499 --> 00:03:50,786
You too, Jee.

62
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:52,287
You should get some rest.

63
00:03:52,287 --> 00:03:55,813
Yeah, it'll be good for me to rest.

64
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:58,200
No more chaos.

65
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:00,736
I can just go anywhere
without a second thought.

66
00:04:00,736 --> 00:04:02,388
No more worrying
about what the shop.

67
00:04:02,388 --> 00:04:04,116
I can go as I please.

68
00:04:05,244 --> 00:04:08,297
Mom, what about that crate?

69
00:04:08,297 --> 00:04:10,243
What are you going to do with it?

70
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:13,550
I don't even know
what crate that is.

71
00:04:13,575 --> 00:04:15,448
It's been there
since the dawn of time.

72
00:04:15,448 --> 00:04:17,115
Go ahead and open it up.

73
00:04:17,115 --> 00:04:19,560
Whatever can be
thrown away, just toss it.

74
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:22,898
And if anything worth donating,
just give it away.

75
00:04:22,923 --> 00:04:24,240
Go on, Ohn.

76
00:04:24,265 --> 00:04:26,212
- Mom...
- What?

77
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:33,390
In the end, it's my job to
clear out your so-called treasure.

78
00:04:33,415 --> 00:04:35,395
Well, if not you, then who?

79
00:04:35,395 --> 00:04:37,480
Why did you keep so much stuff?

80
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:39,693
- I can't even remember.
- Just old keepsakes.

81
00:04:39,693 --> 00:04:42,803
- Why do you keep these?
- Just throw them away.

82
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,486
What's in this box?

83
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:48,402
- Whoa, Mom...
- What?

84
00:04:49,246 --> 00:04:51,663
These are all valuables!

85
00:04:52,093 --> 00:04:54,516
- A gold necklace.
- Wow!

86
00:04:55,406 --> 00:04:57,976
- These are mine?
- You didn't know?

87
00:04:58,001 --> 00:05:01,096
How on earth did I
manage to just toss this aside?

88
00:05:01,858 --> 00:05:04,590
Oh... I remember now.

89
00:05:05,747 --> 00:05:07,141
It belongs to your grandma.

90
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:10,190
It's what she gave your father
to propose to me with.

91
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,440
- Oh.
- Wow.

92
00:05:12,440 --> 00:05:14,960
I tucked it away
and thought I had lost it.

93
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:17,480
Wow...

94
00:05:17,998 --> 00:05:20,607
Ohn, do me a favor.

95
00:05:21,481 --> 00:05:22,481
What is it?

96
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,273
Take these...

97
00:05:25,010 --> 00:05:27,255
and return them to
your grandma in Nakhon Nayok.

98
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:28,603
Come on, Mom.

99
00:05:28,991 --> 00:05:31,849
It's been so long, she's probably
forgotten all about them.

100
00:05:31,874 --> 00:05:34,160
She gave them to you,
so just keep them.

101
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,520
There's no need to return them.

102
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:39,143
So stubborn.
You never do what I ask.

103
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:42,200
You should go visit your grandma,

104
00:05:42,225 --> 00:05:44,490
and bring these back
to her and that...

105
00:05:45,499 --> 00:05:48,123
bring these back
to her and your father.

106
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,960
I don't want
any karmic debt to follow me.

107
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:54,120
Let's end it in this lifetime.

108
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,120
Do you understand?

109
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,080
Yeah.

110
00:05:58,618 --> 00:06:00,800
I completely forgot about this.

111
00:06:01,946 --> 00:06:02,946
Tsk.

112
00:06:16,193 --> 00:06:18,160
Ohn, what's wrong?

113
00:06:20,298 --> 00:06:21,726
What are you worrying about?

114
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,160
It's nothing.

115
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:27,800
I just...

116
00:06:28,714 --> 00:06:30,500
I just don't want to
go to Nakhon Nayok.

117
00:06:34,473 --> 00:06:36,966
About Mom wanting you
to return those things?

118
00:06:39,341 --> 00:06:40,341
Yeah.

119
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,213
Mom is something else...

120
00:06:45,375 --> 00:06:47,770
I asked her to come with us,
but she refused.

121
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:52,080
Then she keeps nagging me,
asking if I've returned them yet.

122
00:06:56,632 --> 00:07:00,560
Should we just send them by mail?

123
00:07:01,176 --> 00:07:04,120
Probably not a good idea.

124
00:07:05,297 --> 00:07:08,880
Since she specifically asked you
to return them and even followed up

125
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:11,463
it must be something
really important to her.

126
00:07:12,263 --> 00:07:13,549
And another thing...

127
00:07:15,396 --> 00:07:17,720
I'm actually very free.

128
00:07:20,513 --> 00:07:22,855
Well, it's good that you're free.

129
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:27,080
You can get some rest,
just like you told my mom.

130
00:07:30,710 --> 00:07:34,157
Closing down is a good thing.
You can finally rest.

131
00:07:34,182 --> 00:07:35,992
- You too, Jee.
- Mmm.

132
00:07:36,017 --> 00:07:37,210
You should get some rest.

133
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:40,216
Should we go tomorrow, then?

134
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,856
I want to see
your grandma's house, too.

135
00:07:45,946 --> 00:07:47,306
Grandma's house...

136
00:07:48,779 --> 00:07:50,080
Dong Lakhon.

137
00:07:54,308 --> 00:07:55,823
Dong Lakhon?

138
00:07:57,133 --> 00:07:58,806
That's where
the ancient city is, right?

139
00:08:00,729 --> 00:08:01,729
Yeah.

140
00:08:03,296 --> 00:08:06,960
I'm curious to see
what it's like these days.

141
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,560
I want to see it too.

142
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:15,620
You should get some sleep.
You have a long drive tomorrow.

143
00:08:16,748 --> 00:08:17,748
Okay.

144
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:27,200
"If it were just
going to Dong Lakhon"

145
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,706
"and seeing Grandma,
that would be nice."

146
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:34,403
"Tonight, I can't sleep again."

147
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:52,190
Hey, don't fall asleep.

148
00:08:53,015 --> 00:08:54,175
It's your old house.

149
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,003
You have to give me directions.

150
00:08:57,400 --> 00:09:00,520
I'm so sleepy.

151
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:05,040
You knew
I couldn't sleep last night.

152
00:09:05,831 --> 00:09:09,385
Stay awake and talk to me.
Don't go falling asleep on me!

153
00:09:09,410 --> 00:09:11,400
Isn't that a bit mean?

154
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:13,080
Sleeping while
I do all the driving?

155
00:09:15,531 --> 00:09:18,047
And look at you, going to see
your grandma and your dad,

156
00:09:18,047 --> 00:09:20,071
but you look so gloomy.

157
00:09:22,653 --> 00:09:25,358
- I do want to see Grandma.
- Mmm.

158
00:09:25,598 --> 00:09:27,320
But whenever I think about Dad,

159
00:09:28,531 --> 00:09:31,600
I feel so heavy.

160
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,316
Race you to the room!

161
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:45,840
I don't believe it.

162
00:09:46,314 --> 00:09:48,695
Don't joke around
about something like this.

163
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:51,086
Believe me.
I saw it with my own eyes.

164
00:09:51,111 --> 00:09:55,463
Are you jealous because
you see us being happy?

165
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:58,030
My husband doesn't have a mistress.

166
00:09:58,810 --> 00:10:01,496
Do you hear me?
My husband doesn't have a mistress!

167
00:10:02,364 --> 00:10:03,600
Calm down, dear.

168
00:10:20,404 --> 00:10:22,991
Aod, you're really seeing
that woman, aren't you?

169
00:10:22,991 --> 00:10:24,097
Answer me!

170
00:10:24,097 --> 00:10:27,175
Ugh, shut up! You keep nagging me.

171
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,255
I have to listen to this nonsense.

172
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,107
I just got back from work,

173
00:10:31,107 --> 00:10:33,440
and then I have to deal with
stupid questions like this?

174
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,293
It's ridiculous. So annoying.

175
00:10:36,984 --> 00:10:37,984
Annoying?

176
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:41,094
If I'm so annoying,
then go live with that woman!

177
00:10:41,119 --> 00:10:43,826
Let me ask you,
the person who told you this,

178
00:10:43,826 --> 00:10:45,400
are they a tick, a mite,

179
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:47,733
or a cockroach
living under the bed?

180
00:10:47,733 --> 00:10:49,613
I can't believe
you'd actually listen to them.

181
00:10:49,613 --> 00:10:52,036
Do you swear to God?

182
00:10:57,379 --> 00:10:58,446
That means...

183
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:03,800
It's true, isn't it?

184
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,280
Isn't it?

185
00:11:06,897 --> 00:11:07,897
Enough!

186
00:11:09,415 --> 00:11:11,200
Where are you going?
We have to settle this.

187
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,860
- Let go of me.
- I won't.

188
00:11:12,860 --> 00:11:14,224
- I said let go of me.
- I won't.

189
00:11:14,224 --> 00:11:15,255
Talk to me!

190
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:17,160
You're not letting go?

191
00:11:18,185 --> 00:11:19,503
You're so damn annoying.

192
00:11:19,528 --> 00:11:21,510
Can't I ever just have
some peace and quiet?

193
00:11:24,450 --> 00:11:27,511
You want me to beat you
every single day, is that it?

194
00:11:27,536 --> 00:11:29,025
You're pathetic.

195
00:11:29,050 --> 00:11:31,295
And how did you raise our son
to turn out like a sissy?

196
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:34,760
A mother like you
is good for absolutely nothing.

197
00:11:50,183 --> 00:11:51,379
Mom...

198
00:11:56,388 --> 00:11:59,895
The father who
wanted me to be strong,

199
00:11:59,920 --> 00:12:01,730
be a real man.

200
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:04,920
Yet he was the one
using force to hurt Mom.

201
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:17,310
It just felt strange
like I'd been betrayed by him.

202
00:12:17,788 --> 00:12:18,788
Mmm.

203
00:12:19,934 --> 00:12:23,310
He didn't live by
the very things he taught me.

204
00:12:24,981 --> 00:12:26,640
What did he try to teach you?

205
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,080
To be a man's man.

206
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,160
Ohn, catch!

207
00:12:35,067 --> 00:12:36,067
Oopsie!

208
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:39,840
Come on. Kick the ball back to me!

209
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:43,203
My little Maradona, come on!

210
00:12:47,360 --> 00:12:49,680
Why are you just standing there?

211
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:51,480
Kick the ball back to me.

212
00:12:52,166 --> 00:12:55,415
Kick it back, my little Maradona.

213
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:57,360
Let's see it.

214
00:12:58,623 --> 00:13:02,194
Why did you kick it that way?
I'm right here!

215
00:13:02,219 --> 00:13:06,479
Why are your arms and legs
so weak and flimsy?

216
00:13:06,479 --> 00:13:08,072
Is that all the strength you have?

217
00:13:08,072 --> 00:13:10,975
We're men.
Put some backbone into it.

218
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:14,847
If people found out that
I have a son this soft and weak,

219
00:13:14,847 --> 00:13:17,295
I'd be so ashamed.
Do you understand?

220
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:20,143
Let's try again.
Concentrate, this time.

221
00:13:20,712 --> 00:13:24,280
Now, catch the ball and juggle it.
Show me what you've got.

222
00:13:24,974 --> 00:13:25,979
Oopsie!

223
00:13:25,979 --> 00:13:28,485
Why are you squealing like that?

224
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,560
Oopsie is for girls.

225
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,280
We're men.
We don't make sounds like that.

226
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:34,120
If I hear that one more time,

227
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:36,486
I'm going to spank you. Got it?

228
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:40,065
I don't want a sissy girly son.

229
00:13:40,065 --> 00:13:43,880
It's ridiculous and embarrassing.
Don't let me hear that again.

230
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:45,317
A sissy son is a joke.

231
00:13:45,317 --> 00:13:47,527
If anyone found out,
I'd never live it down.

232
00:13:47,527 --> 00:13:50,433
- Yes, Dad.
- Go get the ball.

233
00:13:50,433 --> 00:13:52,093
Focus! Be strong!

234
00:13:52,093 --> 00:13:53,900
Show some strength!

235
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:57,152
Much better.
Okay, my little Maradona.

236
00:13:57,152 --> 00:13:58,483
Show me!

237
00:13:59,014 --> 00:14:00,947
Very good.

238
00:14:00,947 --> 00:14:02,971
Yeah, good job.

239
00:14:09,494 --> 00:14:11,892
Should we just
head back to Bangkok?

240
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:13,960
And mail the stuff instead?

241
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,074
Hmm?

242
00:14:19,273 --> 00:14:20,280
No, Jee.

243
00:14:21,683 --> 00:14:25,843
I'm not that kid who's scared of
Dad's threats and shouting anymore.

244
00:14:27,286 --> 00:14:30,560
Even if I'm not
the kind of son he wanted,

245
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:34,840
I'm proud to be exactly who I am.

246
00:14:41,685 --> 00:14:43,625
We'll face this together.

247
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:47,358
The reason I can be this strong

248
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:49,600
is because I have you.

249
00:14:50,453 --> 00:14:51,806
and all my friends.

250
00:14:55,085 --> 00:14:58,266
- Around 8th or 9th grade,
- Mmm-hmm.

251
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:01,060
Mom and Dad finally split up.

252
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:05,440
That's just the Hard-Nights life
for kids like us.

253
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:08,323
You gotta have some problems
to make life interesting.

254
00:15:11,197 --> 00:15:12,873
Don't look so down, Ohn.

255
00:15:13,560 --> 00:15:15,263
Worrying is a waste of time.

256
00:15:16,068 --> 00:15:17,403
Why be in a bad mood?

257
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:22,996
Even if you aren't
living with your dad,

258
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,223
you've still got your mom.

259
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:28,296
You've still got
Aom and Mae Champi.

260
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:31,000
You've got me, Thai, and Chon.

261
00:15:33,408 --> 00:15:35,030
We're all right here with you.

262
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:42,160
Thanks, guys.

263
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:54,853
I have a great family
and great friends,

264
00:15:54,853 --> 00:15:57,560
and a wonderful partner like you.

265
00:15:58,992 --> 00:16:02,983
My mom is great,
my sister is super great

266
00:16:03,393 --> 00:16:05,793
plus I have an amazing nephew.

267
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:10,000
So why should I be afraid
of a past that wasn't so good?

268
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:11,600
Right, Jee?

269
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:14,954
In that case, let's keep going.

270
00:16:14,954 --> 00:16:16,960
Let's go...

271
00:16:17,407 --> 00:16:18,560
Keep going, Jee!

272
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:42,026
Who is that?

273
00:16:57,824 --> 00:16:58,911
Hello, Grandma.

274
00:17:00,085 --> 00:17:01,445
What? Grandma?

275
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:06,160
Ohn?

276
00:17:09,134 --> 00:17:10,326
Hello, Grandma.

277
00:17:12,962 --> 00:17:14,440
There're two of you.

278
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:18,252
Which one is Ohn?

279
00:17:23,044 --> 00:17:24,520
Can you guess?

280
00:17:26,237 --> 00:17:29,295
Don't tease an old woman.

281
00:17:29,320 --> 00:17:33,646
It's been decades.
How could I possibly guess?

282
00:17:33,646 --> 00:17:36,503
Grandma, that hurts my feelings.

283
00:17:37,015 --> 00:17:39,003
Even I still remember you.

284
00:17:49,399 --> 00:17:51,812
Yeah, this one is definitely Ohn.

285
00:17:51,837 --> 00:17:54,896
You're the spitting image
of your father.

286
00:17:55,670 --> 00:17:57,678
You're good.
You actually remembered.

287
00:17:57,678 --> 00:18:02,400
I'm so happy.
Come on, it's hot. Let's go inside.

288
00:18:02,971 --> 00:18:05,084
Careful, Grandma. Watch your step.

289
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:06,307
Come in.

290
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:12,678
Have a seat, dear.

291
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:27,400
Grandma, I saw you limping.

292
00:18:28,100 --> 00:18:29,513
Is something wrong with your leg?

293
00:18:29,513 --> 00:18:32,960
It's just what happens
when you get old, son.

294
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:35,153
A little ache here,
a little pain there.

295
00:18:40,176 --> 00:18:43,640
You're staring. Don't you trust me?

296
00:18:44,120 --> 00:18:47,415
It's really is me. The real Ohn.

297
00:18:47,440 --> 00:18:48,680
Not some stranger.

298
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:52,615
You don't have to worry.
It's really me, Grandma.

299
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:55,440
It's not like that at all, my dear.

300
00:18:55,935 --> 00:18:56,935
You know...

301
00:18:57,864 --> 00:19:03,158
when your mother
took you and Aom away,

302
00:19:03,183 --> 00:19:05,886
I cried every single night.

303
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:13,335
It's been 30, maybe 40, years.

304
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,760
If you don't want
to be with me, then get out!

305
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:20,466
All of you, get out!

306
00:19:21,839 --> 00:19:23,832
If you don't want
to be with me, then get out!

307
00:19:23,832 --> 00:19:25,120
Go!

308
00:19:25,829 --> 00:19:27,702
Take good care of yourself, dear.

309
00:19:29,493 --> 00:19:32,440
- Please look after them.
- Yes, Mother. I'm leaving now.

310
00:19:34,474 --> 00:19:36,918
- Goodbye, children.
- Let's go, kids.

311
00:19:40,349 --> 00:19:41,640
Every last one of you, get out!

312
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:51,120
Go!

313
00:20:03,965 --> 00:20:06,280
I raised you and Aom.

314
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:11,247
I really thought I'd get to
see you both grow up.

315
00:20:11,247 --> 00:20:13,767
But I'm not angry with your mother

316
00:20:13,767 --> 00:20:16,803
for taking you all and
running away from this house.

317
00:20:21,120 --> 00:20:23,940
I missed you so much.

318
00:20:23,940 --> 00:20:25,633
I'm old now.

319
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:28,847
My hearing is fading,
my eyes are failing.

320
00:20:28,847 --> 00:20:31,520
I don't know
when my time will come.

321
00:20:31,520 --> 00:20:34,560
Grandma, don't talk like that.

322
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:39,187
It's all because of your dad,
and his womanizing,

323
00:20:39,187 --> 00:20:41,800
it ruined everything.

324
00:20:43,449 --> 00:20:48,834
But he really did
love you both very much.

325
00:20:48,859 --> 00:20:50,539
Both you and Aom.

326
00:20:55,095 --> 00:20:56,802
- I said let go!
- Talk to me.

327
00:20:56,802 --> 00:20:57,973
You're not letting go?

328
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:01,800
You're so annoying!

329
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:04,430
And how did you raise our son
to turn out like a sissy?

330
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,960
- Oopsie!
- Why are you squealing?

331
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:12,335
If I hear that one more time,

332
00:21:12,360 --> 00:21:14,435
- I'm going to spank you. Got it?
- Yes, Dad.

333
00:21:14,435 --> 00:21:16,235
We're men.
We don't make sounds like that.

334
00:21:20,504 --> 00:21:23,704
I only remember
the good things about you, Grandma.

335
00:21:25,234 --> 00:21:27,495
Yeah, let it be, dear.

336
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:30,942
We're all old now.
We each live our own lives.

337
00:21:30,967 --> 00:21:35,192
No one has to take care of
anyone else anymore, okay?

338
00:21:37,241 --> 00:21:38,241
Yes, Grandma.

339
00:21:58,603 --> 00:22:01,330
Oh my! What is all this treasure?

340
00:22:02,024 --> 00:22:03,344
Mom said...

341
00:22:03,344 --> 00:22:06,712
it's the dowry from when
she and Dad got married.

342
00:22:07,102 --> 00:22:09,400
Goodness, why give them to me?

343
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:12,119
Take them back to your mother.
These are hers.

344
00:22:12,119 --> 00:22:15,033
The way your father
treated your mother

345
00:22:15,033 --> 00:22:17,106
was shameful enough as it is.

346
00:22:17,106 --> 00:22:21,099
But Mom feels uneasy keeping them.
She wanted to return them to you.

347
00:22:21,099 --> 00:22:23,106
You just accept them. Here.

348
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,166
Please?

349
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,680
Just take them back to your mother.

350
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:47,480
Oh, and what about Aom?

351
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:51,203
How is your sister doing?

352
00:22:51,769 --> 00:22:53,782
You don't have to
worry about her at all.

353
00:22:53,782 --> 00:22:55,836
She's doing great.

354
00:22:55,836 --> 00:22:57,920
She got married,
then she got divorced,

355
00:22:57,920 --> 00:23:01,010
now her kid is almost a teenager.

356
00:23:01,395 --> 00:23:05,242
Really? I'd love to
see my great-grandchild.

357
00:23:05,242 --> 00:23:09,802
Tell Aom to come visit me
when she's free. I miss her.

358
00:23:09,802 --> 00:23:13,720
Tell her to call me, okay?
Don't forget to tell her.

359
00:23:13,720 --> 00:23:16,587
I'll tell her
when I get back, Grandma.

360
00:23:16,587 --> 00:23:18,755
I'll have her
bring Ikkyu to visit you.

361
00:23:18,755 --> 00:23:21,428
I guarantee he'll give you
such a headache

362
00:23:21,428 --> 00:23:23,335
you won't have time to be lonely.

363
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:29,080
I should be heading back now.

364
00:23:29,733 --> 00:23:32,732
For goodness sake! Why the rush?

365
00:23:32,757 --> 00:23:34,560
You haven't even seen your father.

366
00:23:40,661 --> 00:23:45,101
Once he's done in the garden,
he's off wandering here and there.

367
00:23:45,101 --> 00:23:47,860
He probably doesn't want to be home
because there's no one here.

368
00:23:47,860 --> 00:23:52,520
No matter how many wives he had,
he'd act out so they all ran away.

369
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:55,495
Leaving only
his old mother to stay with him.

370
00:23:55,520 --> 00:23:59,352
He's not doing too well, either.

371
00:23:59,352 --> 00:24:03,165
Who knows if he's fainted
out there somewhere?

372
00:24:03,165 --> 00:24:05,520
Dad is sick, Grandma?

373
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:10,673
Yeah, he's getting old,
so it's one thing after another.

374
00:24:10,673 --> 00:24:15,240
When he was young, it was booze
and cigarettes every single day.

375
00:24:15,240 --> 00:24:17,713
Now all those illnesses
are catching up with him.

376
00:24:18,272 --> 00:24:19,292
Say...

377
00:24:20,181 --> 00:24:21,780
Why don't you wait for him a bit?

378
00:24:26,146 --> 00:24:28,753
Um, Ohn and I were planning
to go for a look around

379
00:24:28,753 --> 00:24:30,960
and walk through
Dong Lakhon for a bit.

380
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:33,313
That's right, Grandma.

381
00:24:33,708 --> 00:24:36,855
Jee has never been there.
He's only heard the name.

382
00:24:36,855 --> 00:24:39,083
So he wanted to see the real place.

383
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:41,960
You aren't afraid anymore?

384
00:24:44,069 --> 00:24:45,069
Afraid?

385
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:47,696
Was I ever afraid
of something there?

386
00:25:02,096 --> 00:25:03,223
Ohn! Ohn!

387
00:25:04,240 --> 00:25:05,680
Wait for me!

388
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:08,960
Wait!

389
00:25:10,144 --> 00:25:12,770
- Whoa!
- Take these to your mother.

390
00:25:12,795 --> 00:25:15,123
- Grandma, what is all this?
- Take them.

391
00:25:15,123 --> 00:25:17,990
- Let me help you.
- There's marian plum,

392
00:25:17,990 --> 00:25:20,111
and pickled bamboo shoots
the locals made.

393
00:25:20,111 --> 00:25:22,515
These are all
your mother's favorites.

394
00:25:22,540 --> 00:25:24,820
- Thank you, Grandma.
- I'll put them in the car.

395
00:25:24,820 --> 00:25:26,920
Oh, and one more thing...

396
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:31,040
I want to
give you this as a keepsake.

397
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:33,400
Keep it safe, okay?

398
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:46,063
What's the deal with this necklace?

399
00:25:47,920 --> 00:25:51,680
It looks familiar.
Like I've seen it somewhere before.

400
00:25:52,579 --> 00:25:54,099
But holding it feels...

401
00:25:54,644 --> 00:25:57,400
- it's giving me the creeps.
- Oh...

402
00:25:57,400 --> 00:26:01,360
It's probably
an antique from Dong Lakhon.

403
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:04,080
Shouldn't we give it to your mom?

404
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:06,216
So she can be the one
getting the creeps instead.

405
00:26:12,333 --> 00:26:13,333
But...

406
00:26:14,906 --> 00:26:15,946
I'm scared.

407
00:26:18,326 --> 00:26:19,361
Scared?

408
00:26:20,830 --> 00:26:23,200
Scared of Dong Lakhon? Why?

409
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:28,001
Don't you remember?

410
00:26:28,001 --> 00:26:32,440
When you were little, you went
to play football around Dong Lakhon

411
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,907
and you went missing for days.

412
00:26:34,907 --> 00:26:38,575
Your parents almost
cried themselves to death.

413
00:26:38,600 --> 00:26:40,139
And once you finally came back

414
00:26:40,803 --> 00:26:44,383
you never go near
Dong Lakhon ever again.

415
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:47,320
Really, Grandma?

416
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:49,640
I don't remember that at all.

417
00:26:53,080 --> 00:26:55,047
I'm not afraid of
Dong Lakhon anymore.

418
00:26:55,047 --> 00:26:56,920
- Mmm-hmm.
- It's just...

419
00:26:58,428 --> 00:27:00,428
I'm afraid of running into Dad.

420
00:27:02,678 --> 00:27:07,396
Grandma said he likes to go
for walks there quite often.

421
00:27:07,939 --> 00:27:08,939
Mmm.

422
00:27:12,381 --> 00:27:13,587
So be it.

423
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:16,033
Right? It'll be exciting.

424
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:22,320
I'm not even sure...

425
00:27:23,480 --> 00:27:26,760
if he knows that I'm gay.

426
00:27:28,628 --> 00:27:31,960
And having to come out
to him at this age,

427
00:27:32,776 --> 00:27:34,556
just the thought of it
gives me chills.

428
00:27:35,442 --> 00:27:36,509
Mmm.

429
00:27:37,015 --> 00:27:39,200
Why worry about it?

430
00:27:39,967 --> 00:27:41,823
You've got Jira
right here with you.

431
00:27:42,538 --> 00:27:45,074
Everything will be okay, alright?

432
00:27:47,628 --> 00:27:48,668
Yeah, you're right.

433
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:53,440
I honestly don't know
what I'd do without you.

434
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:58,000
Whenever I have a problem,
you're always my safe zone.

435
00:28:01,131 --> 00:28:02,280
Come to think of it...

436
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:05,396
I feel sorry for single people.

437
00:28:08,122 --> 00:28:09,480
Oh, please!

438
00:28:10,464 --> 00:28:11,517
Look at you!

439
00:28:54,019 --> 00:28:55,019
Let's go.

440
00:28:57,292 --> 00:28:59,317
- This way?
- Mmm.

441
00:29:03,552 --> 00:29:04,760
Wow!

442
00:29:05,343 --> 00:29:07,160
- It's so nice here.
- Right?

443
00:29:10,167 --> 00:29:11,167
Here...

444
00:29:12,199 --> 00:29:13,800
Seeing it for real.

445
00:29:14,858 --> 00:29:16,520
Is it like what you remembered?

446
00:29:18,490 --> 00:29:19,490
Hmm.

447
00:29:20,560 --> 00:29:22,240
Not exactly.

448
00:29:23,436 --> 00:29:26,378
In the past, it looked
all messy and cluttered.

449
00:29:26,378 --> 00:29:28,076
But they've renovated it now.

450
00:29:28,101 --> 00:29:30,185
It's much more organized.

451
00:29:30,568 --> 00:29:31,568
Mmm.

452
00:29:35,640 --> 00:29:36,800
- Look.
- Huh?

453
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,663
I've got goosebumps.

454
00:29:39,062 --> 00:29:41,080
Or do you need to use the toilet?

455
00:29:41,905 --> 00:29:44,302
I already took care of that.

456
00:29:44,327 --> 00:29:45,480
I see.

457
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:49,440
Dad?

458
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:55,840
Whose dad?

459
00:29:59,244 --> 00:30:03,615
Sorry. I thought
you were my father.

460
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,920
I haven't seen him in a long time.

461
00:30:05,945 --> 00:30:09,800
No worries. I thought
I'd gained another son!

462
00:30:12,280 --> 00:30:13,960
Are you two here for a visit?

463
00:30:14,365 --> 00:30:15,392
Yes, sir.

464
00:30:15,392 --> 00:30:17,765
Feel free to roam about.

465
00:30:17,765 --> 00:30:19,492
I'm a local.

466
00:30:19,492 --> 00:30:21,024
- I see.
- Mmm.

467
00:30:21,024 --> 00:30:23,044
I used to live around here.

468
00:30:23,044 --> 00:30:25,164
But I've been in Bangkok
for a long time now.

469
00:30:25,164 --> 00:30:28,680
I'm back in town for some business,
so I stopped by to look around.

470
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:30,620
I've lived here since I was born.

471
00:30:30,620 --> 00:30:34,245
I like walking here
because it's cool and pleasant.

472
00:30:34,245 --> 00:30:35,320
Yes.

473
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:37,880
It's not scary at all,
unlike what people say.

474
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:42,280
What are the rumors, sir?

475
00:30:43,206 --> 00:30:44,486
Who knows who started it...

476
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:48,800
saying the Dong Lakhon ancient city

477
00:30:49,149 --> 00:30:51,356
is a mysterious
and terrifying place.

478
00:30:52,015 --> 00:30:54,610
Now all the local kids
are scared of it, too.

479
00:30:55,600 --> 00:30:57,527
The tourists have all vanished.

480
00:30:57,527 --> 00:31:00,360
The street vendors
had all gone broke.

481
00:31:00,831 --> 00:31:01,960
Mmm...

482
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:04,120
It's that bad?

483
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:08,200
Is any of it true?

484
00:31:08,925 --> 00:31:12,712
What would there be?
I walk through here all the time.

485
00:31:12,712 --> 00:31:14,771
It's just an old, ancient city.

486
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:20,356
What about people hearing
Thai music at night?

487
00:31:20,381 --> 00:31:23,636
There's probably just
a Thai music teacher

488
00:31:24,360 --> 00:31:27,000
- teaching songs to students.
- Hmm.

489
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:28,220
It's quiet here.

490
00:31:29,653 --> 00:31:33,820
A little bit of music will echo
through the whole neighborhood.

491
00:31:35,040 --> 00:31:36,960
Those who obsessed
with the supernatural,

492
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,987
they're just imagining things.

493
00:31:38,987 --> 00:31:40,493
Just overactive imaginations.

494
00:31:42,120 --> 00:31:46,120
I remember there being a well.
Where is it?

495
00:31:46,880 --> 00:31:51,083
Over there. Follow this path;
you can't miss it.

496
00:31:51,888 --> 00:31:54,160
Enjoy your walk.

497
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:56,160
I'll be wandering around here too.

498
00:31:56,520 --> 00:31:59,824
If you loop around, we'll probably
run into each other again.

499
00:31:59,849 --> 00:32:00,856
Yes.

500
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:02,286
- Thank you very much.
- Thank you.

501
00:32:02,286 --> 00:32:03,578
Yes, goodbye.

502
00:32:03,578 --> 00:32:05,320
Go on, then.

503
00:32:35,648 --> 00:32:36,840
- Jee...
- Hmm?

504
00:32:37,398 --> 00:32:39,463
I was just scared half to death.

505
00:32:40,432 --> 00:32:43,323
- Mmm-hmm.
- I thought I'd run into Dad.

506
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:46,576
So what?
I'll be right by your side.

507
00:32:47,070 --> 00:32:48,760
We'll get through it together.

508
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:54,320
Oh...

509
00:33:01,206 --> 00:33:03,362
- They've done a great job here.
- Mmm.

510
00:33:03,362 --> 00:33:05,488
There are actual pillars
and a proper roof.

511
00:33:05,488 --> 00:33:06,528
Mmm.

512
00:33:07,474 --> 00:33:09,028
From what I remember...

513
00:33:09,974 --> 00:33:10,974
back in the day...

514
00:33:12,480 --> 00:33:15,760
it was just a well right here.

515
00:33:16,480 --> 00:33:17,480
And...

516
00:33:18,333 --> 00:33:20,613
The forest around here
was completely overgrown.

517
00:33:21,109 --> 00:33:22,109
Hmm.

518
00:33:24,906 --> 00:33:26,400
Wow...

519
00:33:58,032 --> 00:34:00,032
- Who might you be?
- Huh?

520
00:34:00,032 --> 00:34:01,243
Never have I seen your face.

521
00:34:01,243 --> 00:34:03,379
Perchance you are
an outsider wandering in?

522
00:34:03,379 --> 00:34:06,039
What do you mean?

523
00:34:06,039 --> 00:34:08,532
Are you a local kid
from Dong Lakhon?

524
00:34:08,532 --> 00:34:10,099
What's Dong Lakhon?

525
00:34:10,099 --> 00:34:11,840
You know, the Ancient City.

526
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:14,000
This used to be an old city.

527
00:34:15,959 --> 00:34:19,120
We are the folk of the Hidden City,

528
00:34:19,120 --> 00:34:21,318
though you may call it Dong Lakhon.

529
00:34:21,318 --> 00:34:22,498
The Hidden City?

530
00:34:22,498 --> 00:34:25,360
Indeed. Though we are
neither ghosts nor spirits.

531
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:28,940
The magic of this realm allows
one to change form they desire.

532
00:34:28,940 --> 00:34:32,120
I saw with my own eyes
your hair grow long

533
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:34,073
and your voice change
from man to woman.

534
00:34:34,073 --> 00:34:36,545
This is what your heart desires.

535
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,040
How is this possible?

536
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:42,101
Have I really turned into a girl?

537
00:34:42,126 --> 00:34:43,895
Does it please you?

538
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:47,129
I love it.
But I don't think my dad would.

539
00:34:48,145 --> 00:34:50,901
This city has everything
you'll ever need.

540
00:34:50,901 --> 00:34:53,205
No need to return to your father.

541
00:34:58,441 --> 00:35:00,999
Little miss from the world beyond,
what is your name?

542
00:35:00,999 --> 00:35:02,046
It's Ohn.

543
00:35:02,046 --> 00:35:04,000
Little Miss Ohn, my name is Ai Rib.

544
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:06,183
Rib? What kind of name is Rib?

545
00:35:06,208 --> 00:35:08,640
Rib as in the fading light of dusk.

546
00:35:08,640 --> 00:35:11,400
My mother gave me this name for
I was born in the twilight hour.

547
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:15,360
Wow! That bead necklace is so chic!

548
00:35:15,360 --> 00:35:17,442
Your words are hard to fathom.

549
00:35:17,442 --> 00:35:20,160
I presume you are fond
of this string of beads?

550
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:22,036
Yes, Brother. I likes it.

551
00:35:22,036 --> 00:35:25,120
Beaded strings in the Hidden City
are found in great abundance.

552
00:35:25,120 --> 00:35:28,840
Should you desire one,
I shall gift it to you.

553
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:33,040
This city, the founding sovereign
was a powerful Queen.

554
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:35,680
Eh? The ruler was a woman?

555
00:35:35,680 --> 00:35:39,487
Here, women hold the power,
not like the world you came from.

556
00:35:39,487 --> 00:35:43,120
You've vanished like this.
Your parents must be worried.

557
00:35:43,120 --> 00:35:47,173
Now that you have played your fill,
you must return to your own world.

558
00:35:47,760 --> 00:35:51,800
I doubt it.
Mom and Dad still have my sister.

559
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:54,307
I'm a pretty useless son anyway.

560
00:35:54,307 --> 00:35:56,640
If one of us goes missing,
it probably won't matter.

561
00:35:57,520 --> 00:36:00,920
Ohn! Where are you, son?

562
00:36:04,160 --> 00:36:07,015
Ai Rib, that's my mother's voices!

563
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,600
Little Miss Ohn, consider this.

564
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:11,740
Your parents have not ignored you,
nor do they lack love for you.

565
00:36:11,740 --> 00:36:15,735
Have pity upon them.
Go back to their side at once.

566
00:36:15,760 --> 00:36:19,736
In that case, I'm going back
to my father and mother.

567
00:36:23,165 --> 00:36:26,992
Ohn! Ohn!

568
00:36:26,992 --> 00:36:29,012
Ohn, where are you?

569
00:36:29,012 --> 00:36:33,731
Ohn! Ohn!

570
00:36:34,219 --> 00:36:35,880
Ohn, can you hear me, son?

571
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:41,116
Ohn, where are you?
Come out, son!

572
00:36:43,591 --> 00:36:45,306
Come to Grandma, please!

573
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:48,920
- Ohn, can you hear me?
- Ohn!

574
00:36:49,830 --> 00:36:51,640
Dad's right here. Can you hear me?

575
00:36:52,520 --> 00:36:53,520
Ohn! Ohn!

576
00:36:54,353 --> 00:36:57,120
- Ohn!
- Where are you? Come out, son!

577
00:36:57,680 --> 00:36:59,215
Ohn, where are you?

578
00:36:59,240 --> 00:37:00,560
Ohn! Ohn!

579
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:04,280
Where are you? Come out, son!

580
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,810
Ohn, come to Grandma!

581
00:37:08,919 --> 00:37:09,919
Ohn!

582
00:37:11,904 --> 00:37:13,200
Come to Grandma!

583
00:37:13,200 --> 00:37:16,950
O sacred spirits
who dwell within this place,

584
00:37:18,819 --> 00:37:21,623
if I have committed any offense

585
00:37:23,006 --> 00:37:24,653
or have done anything wrong,

586
00:37:25,413 --> 00:37:28,253
I beg your forgiveness
and mercy right here and now.

587
00:37:28,819 --> 00:37:30,257
Please, I beseech you...

588
00:37:30,878 --> 00:37:34,383
Guide me so that I may find Ohn...

589
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:38,120
My son. Please let me find him.

590
00:37:41,569 --> 00:37:44,061
- We found him!
- Ohn!

591
00:37:44,431 --> 00:37:45,431
Ohn!

592
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:48,720
Ohn, my son!

593
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:50,920
Ohn!

594
00:37:50,944 --> 00:37:52,370
Ohn, my baby!

595
00:37:52,395 --> 00:37:53,435
Ohn, Dad's here!

596
00:37:53,768 --> 00:37:54,775
Ohn!

597
00:38:04,487 --> 00:38:05,872
Are you okay, son?

598
00:38:07,208 --> 00:38:08,208
Dad's here.

599
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,280
Mom, he's burning up!

600
00:38:14,175 --> 00:38:16,655
We need to get him to the hospital.

601
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:18,400
Hang in there, sweetheart.

602
00:38:18,425 --> 00:38:20,200
I'm taking you to the doctor.

603
00:38:20,200 --> 00:38:21,720
Hurry up!

604
00:38:27,672 --> 00:38:29,007
Out of the way!

605
00:38:29,032 --> 00:38:30,560
Step aside, please!

606
00:38:35,821 --> 00:38:36,821
Ohn.

607
00:38:40,206 --> 00:38:41,280
Ohn!

608
00:38:41,534 --> 00:38:42,567
Did you hear me?

609
00:38:42,567 --> 00:38:44,993
Why are you shouting?
You scared the life out of me!

610
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:48,400
Hey, I remember now.

611
00:38:48,933 --> 00:38:51,880
About what Grandma said,
why I was afraid of Dong Lakhon.

612
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:53,480
It's because when I was a kid,

613
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:56,400
I actually got lost
in the woods around here.

614
00:38:58,357 --> 00:39:02,950
After that, Dad forbade me
from coming back to Dong Lakhon.

615
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:06,520
He told me that this place
was haunted by ghosts.

616
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:11,691
So I grew up fearing Dong Lakhon
all because of Dad's lies.

617
00:39:11,691 --> 00:39:12,720
Mmm-hmm.

618
00:39:14,197 --> 00:39:15,664
It looks pretty normal to me.

619
00:39:15,664 --> 00:39:19,040
It doesn't look like a place
where you'd easily get lost.

620
00:39:20,560 --> 00:39:22,160
Exactly.

621
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:24,689
That's why I said it felt strange.

622
00:39:27,316 --> 00:39:29,040
But then again, when we're kids,

623
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:31,800
everything looks much bigger
than it really is.

624
00:39:32,702 --> 00:39:34,600
So you could get lost
back then, right?

625
00:39:35,209 --> 00:39:36,269
Hey!

626
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,760
Hey, wait for me!

627
00:39:40,905 --> 00:39:41,905
Ohn.

628
00:39:46,112 --> 00:39:47,112
Ohn.

629
00:40:02,080 --> 00:40:03,080
You know?

630
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:08,280
For a child of divorced parents,

631
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:11,193
there's often a deep emotional scar

632
00:40:11,193 --> 00:40:13,573
that makes them
fearful of new relationships,

633
00:40:14,480 --> 00:40:15,480
in a way...

634
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,880
that other children
will never understand.

635
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:21,680
Mmm-hmm.

636
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:23,244
It's like...

637
00:40:24,320 --> 00:40:27,000
being betrayed by the person
you love most in the world.

638
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:31,600
- When I think about Dad...
- Mmm-hmm.

639
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:35,040
it's this mix of feelings of
both positive or negative.

640
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:36,040
Mmm.

641
00:40:37,400 --> 00:40:43,425
Dad left behind a deep and
massive scar when it comes to love.

642
00:40:43,425 --> 00:40:44,545
Mmm-hmm.

643
00:40:44,545 --> 00:40:47,320
It's why whenever I start
to feel something for someone,

644
00:40:48,160 --> 00:40:51,480
I just instinctively pull away.

645
00:40:53,480 --> 00:40:54,480
And...

646
00:40:55,324 --> 00:40:56,636
Do you realize now?

647
00:40:57,207 --> 00:41:00,593
That someone
trustworthy actually exists?

648
00:41:04,260 --> 00:41:07,990
Well, it took me
a long time to find you.

649
00:41:08,688 --> 00:41:13,080
And letting myself believe in you?
That wasn't easy, either.

650
00:41:13,105 --> 00:41:14,105
Mmm-hmm.

651
00:41:16,587 --> 00:41:17,960
- Do you know?
- Hmm?

652
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:21,160
What you give me is warmth.

653
00:41:22,000 --> 00:41:24,118
- And trust.
- Mmm-hmm.

654
00:41:24,540 --> 00:41:26,543
It makes me feel...

655
00:41:27,040 --> 00:41:28,590
we can actually be together.

656
00:41:30,160 --> 00:41:32,360
I feel secure.

657
00:41:36,464 --> 00:41:37,464
Secure, huh?

658
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:39,400
Yeah.

659
00:41:41,446 --> 00:41:44,800
Quitting my job, I have no idea
where I'm going to find security.

660
00:41:58,493 --> 00:41:59,893
Watch out for the thorns.

661
00:41:59,893 --> 00:42:01,626
Watch out!

662
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:05,240
This way.

663
00:42:05,240 --> 00:42:07,893
I don't know
if this is the right way.

664
00:42:07,893 --> 00:42:09,993
Watch the thorns!

665
00:42:09,993 --> 00:42:11,433
Ow, wait, wait!

666
00:42:11,433 --> 00:42:12,729
Did it get you?

667
00:42:12,729 --> 00:42:14,353
You okay?

668
00:42:16,283 --> 00:42:17,442
Is this the way?

669
00:42:20,093 --> 00:42:22,840
- Is this really the way, Jee?
- I don't know.

670
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:24,585
It doesn't look familiar.

671
00:42:30,778 --> 00:42:31,784
Careful.

672
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:33,560
Jee...

673
00:42:35,040 --> 00:42:36,360
I can't walk anymore.

674
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:39,380
Just leave me here.

675
00:42:40,280 --> 00:42:42,640
Find a way out of these woods
and save yourself.

676
00:42:43,073 --> 00:42:44,140
Come on, Ohn.

677
00:42:48,611 --> 00:42:51,320
You've been watching
too many dramas. Look over there.

678
00:42:52,960 --> 00:42:53,960
Help us!

679
00:42:55,967 --> 00:42:57,960
Help!

680
00:42:59,705 --> 00:43:01,230
Help us, please!

681
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:06,100
- Sir, we're lost in the woods.
- Oh! We meet again.

682
00:43:06,100 --> 00:43:07,840
I thought
we were going to die in here.

683
00:43:07,840 --> 00:43:08,993
Lost?

684
00:43:08,993 --> 00:43:11,379
The exit is right here.
It's not far at all.

685
00:43:12,674 --> 00:43:13,674
Dad.

686
00:43:14,042 --> 00:43:16,335
He looks thirsty.
Like he's about to faint.

687
00:43:17,320 --> 00:43:19,440
Should we give him some cold water?

688
00:43:19,465 --> 00:43:20,800
Go ahead, son.

689
00:43:21,373 --> 00:43:24,520
- Help me out.
- Yeah, give them some water.

690
00:43:25,115 --> 00:43:26,760
- Here. Take it easy.
- Here you go.

691
00:43:26,760 --> 00:43:28,653
- Thank you so much.
- Drink some water.

692
00:43:29,208 --> 00:43:31,128
You'll feel better.
The way out is right there.

693
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,479
- I'm okay now. Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

694
00:43:42,487 --> 00:43:44,455
None of this looks familiar.

695
00:43:44,480 --> 00:43:49,022
It might be right.
He pointed this way.

696
00:43:49,047 --> 00:43:51,023
- There, over there!
- Where?

697
00:43:53,016 --> 00:43:54,530
The parking lot!

698
00:43:56,352 --> 00:43:58,400
- We made it!
- Let's go.

699
00:44:07,480 --> 00:44:08,480
Dad.

700
00:44:10,186 --> 00:44:11,186
Hey!

701
00:44:12,100 --> 00:44:13,100
Ohn?

702
00:44:13,428 --> 00:44:14,480
Is that really you, Ohn?

703
00:44:15,311 --> 00:44:16,311
My son.

704
00:44:18,148 --> 00:44:19,480
- Hello, Dad.
- Hello, sir.

705
00:44:20,452 --> 00:44:22,872
Your grandma called and
told me you were coming.

706
00:44:22,872 --> 00:44:25,118
I've been walking around
looking for you for a while.

707
00:44:26,527 --> 00:44:29,880
But are you leaving already?

708
00:44:32,440 --> 00:44:34,398
- Yes, Dad.
- Mmm.

709
00:44:34,719 --> 00:44:38,188
Did you come back because
you wanted to see me, son?

710
00:44:39,684 --> 00:44:42,520
Is that it, son?

711
00:44:45,320 --> 00:44:46,320
Is it?

712
00:44:47,671 --> 00:44:48,768
No, Dad.

713
00:44:49,182 --> 00:44:52,240
I just came to return the things
Grandma once gave to Mom.

714
00:45:07,910 --> 00:45:09,000
I miss you.

715
00:45:09,728 --> 00:45:11,018
I miss everyone.

716
00:45:11,018 --> 00:45:13,042
You, Aom...

717
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:15,080
and your mother.

718
00:45:16,072 --> 00:45:17,440
But I didn't dare reach out.

719
00:45:17,440 --> 00:45:19,252
I didn't know
if you were all still angry.

720
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:27,000
I'm sorry for
all the trouble I caused.

721
00:45:31,038 --> 00:45:32,311
You actually realize that?

722
00:45:34,684 --> 00:45:37,560
Of course I do. I just hope
you don't end up like me.

723
00:45:41,120 --> 00:45:42,920
There's no way
I'll ever be like you.

724
00:45:46,198 --> 00:45:47,357
That's for the best.

725
00:45:48,680 --> 00:45:50,066
Don't be like me, son.

726
00:45:52,538 --> 00:45:54,272
I said let go of me!

727
00:45:54,801 --> 00:45:56,880
Do you want me to
beat you every single day?

728
00:45:57,949 --> 00:46:00,996
And how did you
raise our son to be a sissy?

729
00:46:00,996 --> 00:46:03,760
A mother like you
is useless at everything.

730
00:46:06,509 --> 00:46:08,800
Otherwise, you'll end up
growing old and dying alone.

731
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:17,782
Those wild jujubes,
they're our specialty here.

732
00:46:18,574 --> 00:46:19,640
Have you ever tried them?

733
00:46:20,274 --> 00:46:22,200
- No, sir.
- Try one.

734
00:46:22,408 --> 00:46:25,640
These are rare. You won't
find them anywhere else.

735
00:46:25,665 --> 00:46:27,000
Mmm, okay.

736
00:46:30,240 --> 00:46:33,200
Is that young man your boyfriend?

737
00:46:33,450 --> 00:46:35,400
Yes. I'm Jira.

738
00:46:36,572 --> 00:46:37,612
I'm Ohn's boyfriend, sir.

739
00:46:43,689 --> 00:46:44,689
Dad...

740
00:46:47,607 --> 00:46:48,680
I'm sorry.

741
00:46:50,357 --> 00:46:52,370
That I couldn't be the kind of man

742
00:46:53,813 --> 00:46:55,373
that you wanted me to be.

743
00:46:56,760 --> 00:46:58,779
Be strong! Show some strength!

744
00:46:58,779 --> 00:47:00,720
Very good. Okay.

745
00:47:00,720 --> 00:47:03,480
My little Maradona, come on!

746
00:47:06,497 --> 00:47:07,890
Like I said...

747
00:47:08,520 --> 00:47:09,920
Don't be like me.

748
00:47:10,703 --> 00:47:14,836
The drinking,
the womanizing, the violence,

749
00:47:14,861 --> 00:47:16,360
none of that is worth following.

750
00:47:20,461 --> 00:47:22,168
Young man...

751
00:47:22,168 --> 00:47:24,490
please take good care of my son.

752
00:47:26,875 --> 00:47:29,683
- You can count on it, sir.
- Mmm. Thank you.

753
00:47:31,695 --> 00:47:34,802
Getting a bit teary-eyed, are we?

754
00:47:34,802 --> 00:47:37,066
Hey, this is my Ohn, alright.

755
00:47:37,066 --> 00:47:38,986
The real deal.

756
00:47:41,355 --> 00:47:42,561
My son.

757
00:47:45,276 --> 00:47:46,396
I'm sorry.

758
00:47:51,360 --> 00:47:52,513
I'm so sorry.

759
00:48:16,149 --> 00:48:17,320
I'm scared, Jee.

760
00:48:18,600 --> 00:48:19,760
Holding it...

761
00:48:20,520 --> 00:48:22,120
It's giving me the creeps.

762
00:48:22,145 --> 00:48:23,701
Beaded strings in the Hidden City

763
00:48:23,701 --> 00:48:25,920
Should you desire one,

764
00:48:25,920 --> 00:48:27,360
I shall gift it to you.

765
00:48:27,364 --> 00:48:29,487
Come to Grandma!

766
00:48:29,512 --> 00:48:31,480
Can you hear me, son?

767
00:48:32,232 --> 00:48:33,352
Ohn! Ohn!

768
00:48:34,547 --> 00:48:35,704
Ohn!

769
00:48:52,840 --> 00:48:54,480
Is that you, Little Miss Ohn?

770
00:48:54,480 --> 00:48:57,120
Ai Rib, look at you!

771
00:48:57,140 --> 00:48:59,480
Still as handsome as ever.
You haven't aged at all.

772
00:48:59,480 --> 00:49:02,173
I just keep getting older.

773
00:49:02,173 --> 00:49:06,140
Many days and nights have passed,
yet you have not forgotten me.

774
00:49:06,140 --> 00:49:07,480
My heart is truly full.

775
00:49:07,480 --> 00:49:10,720
I'm glad
you haven't forgotten me either.

776
00:49:10,720 --> 00:49:12,144
I've come to say goodbye.

777
00:49:12,144 --> 00:49:14,168
I probably won't be
coming back here again.

778
00:49:18,447 --> 00:49:22,388
May Little Miss Ohn find
happiness with the one you love.

779
00:49:24,080 --> 00:49:25,080
Ohn.

780
00:49:25,893 --> 00:49:26,893
Ohn.

781
00:49:28,343 --> 00:49:29,343
Ohn.

782
00:49:29,937 --> 00:49:30,937
Ohn.

783
00:49:31,234 --> 00:49:32,354
What happened?

784
00:49:32,820 --> 00:49:35,150
Suddenly, you passed out.

785
00:49:35,847 --> 00:49:38,386
I thought you were leaving me.

786
00:49:41,760 --> 00:49:44,400
I tried putting on the necklace.

787
00:49:45,008 --> 00:49:47,999
And then I warped
back to the Hidden City,

788
00:49:47,999 --> 00:49:49,652
just like when I was a kid.

789
00:49:49,652 --> 00:49:51,840
You've got to be kidding me.

790
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:54,310
You were burning up.

791
00:49:56,518 --> 00:49:58,770
I was just in a bit of a daze.

792
00:49:59,378 --> 00:50:00,944
It was some Narnia-level fantasy.

793
00:50:02,049 --> 00:50:05,200
But I don't think
I'll be going back there again.

794
00:50:05,796 --> 00:50:08,800
It's likely just a fever dream.

795
00:50:09,400 --> 00:50:12,000
Can you stand up?
Should we go to the hospital?

796
00:50:12,306 --> 00:50:13,373
Hmm?

797
00:50:13,620 --> 00:50:14,893
No need.

798
00:50:14,893 --> 00:50:17,152
I'm okay. I feel fine now.

799
00:50:17,457 --> 00:50:18,750
- You sure?
- Mmm-hmm.

800
00:51:03,120 --> 00:51:06,440
I'm glad you told me to return
those things to Grandma.

801
00:51:06,440 --> 00:51:08,367
Because of that,
I actually got to see Dad.

802
00:51:08,960 --> 00:51:10,600
And you got to talk to him.

803
00:51:12,419 --> 00:51:15,177
It feels like
I've finally unlocked something.

804
00:51:18,320 --> 00:51:19,320
From now on...

805
00:51:20,600 --> 00:51:23,880
Dad won't be a gray area
in my life anymore.

806
00:51:25,741 --> 00:51:26,854
Mmm.

807
00:51:26,854 --> 00:51:30,248
And if you ever want to visit
Dad and Grandma again,

808
00:51:30,248 --> 00:51:32,535
just say the word
and I'll drive you here.

809
00:51:32,560 --> 00:51:34,920
I like the weather here.

810
00:51:36,498 --> 00:51:38,080
Thank you so much, Jee.

811
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:41,080
Please keep being
this sweet to me forever.

812
00:51:42,461 --> 00:51:43,560
Forever.

813
00:51:47,036 --> 00:51:50,440
How about we stay
the night at Grandma's?

814
00:51:50,440 --> 00:51:52,760
I'll go butter her up

815
00:51:52,760 --> 00:51:55,500
and have her cook us
a massive feast.

816
00:51:55,525 --> 00:51:57,792
Yeah let's do that.

817
00:51:57,792 --> 00:51:58,898
Mmm.

818
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:11,520
Actually, maybe next time?

819
00:52:12,440 --> 00:52:14,240
I'm afraid
my fever might come back.

820
00:52:14,900 --> 00:52:15,933
Mmm-hmm.

821
00:52:15,933 --> 00:52:19,040
We'd better not disturb
the music teachers around here.

822
00:52:20,160 --> 00:52:21,160
Mmm-hmm.

823
00:52:21,487 --> 00:52:22,606
Let's go.

824
00:52:48,869 --> 00:52:50,480
If I still can't draw,

825
00:52:52,160 --> 00:52:53,315
then I'm really quitting.

826
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:56,320
What should I do, Jee?

827
00:52:57,173 --> 00:52:59,733
I have no energy to work at all.

828
00:53:01,420 --> 00:53:02,780
And, action!

829
00:53:03,120 --> 00:53:05,513
When I was a kid,
I loved traditional dance.

830
00:53:05,513 --> 00:53:07,560
I wanted to be a star.

831
00:53:07,560 --> 00:53:10,400
I wanted to be
a national volleyball player.

832
00:53:11,028 --> 00:53:12,400
Take the team to the Olympics.

833
00:53:12,880 --> 00:53:15,800
When I was a kid, my dream was...

834
00:53:16,400 --> 00:53:17,720
to get married,

835
00:53:18,880 --> 00:53:19,880
and have kids.

836
00:53:25,133 --> 00:53:26,193
Don't be naughty!

837
00:53:26,606 --> 00:53:27,653
Look at that!

838
00:53:29,560 --> 00:53:32,320
When you flip through it fast,
it starts to move.

839
00:53:32,720 --> 00:53:33,720
Look!

840
00:53:43,935 --> 00:53:49,095
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

841
00:53:49,120 --> 00:53:55,400
♪ Can you feel
the stories we made? ♪

842
00:53:55,400 --> 00:54:00,540
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

843
00:54:00,540 --> 00:54:04,093
♪ Come rain or shine ♪

844
00:54:04,093 --> 00:54:09,360
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

845
00:54:09,360 --> 00:54:15,560
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

846
00:54:15,560 --> 00:54:20,800
♪ Calling out so we never part ♪

847
00:54:21,680 --> 00:54:25,800
♪ Every day together
just you and I ♪

848
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:30,760
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

849
00:54:30,760 --> 00:54:35,640
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

850
